full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/11/2023 IN THE SUPREME COURT OF QUEENSLAND In Matrimonial Jurisdiction No. 340 of 1960. The Chief Justice Mr. Justice Philp BETWEEN RUBY ELSIE JOSEFI PLAINTIFF AND MICHAEL JOSEFI DEFENDANT THE SEVENTEENTH DAY OF FEBRUARY, 1961 UPON HEARING the request filed herein this day that the Judgement Nisi granted in this action on the Twentysixth day of October 1960 be made Absolute and UPON READING the said Judgement Nisi and the Affidavit of NEIL JOLYON BREEN filed herein this day and no cause being shown to the contrary THIS COURT DOTH ORDER AND ADJUDGE that the marriage solemnised on the Sixteenth day of May 1934 at the office of the Registrar of Marriages in Collins Street, Melbourne in the State of Victoria by Percy Filmore Clarke, according to law between the abovenamed RUBY ELSIE JOSEFI and the abovenamed MICHAEL JOSEFI shall be and the same is hereby dissolved. BY THE COURT (L.S.) E. P. Laracy SECOND DEPUTY REGISTRAR Original see and returned SFP 221957 Beguall Pur
